  "body": "\r\n### Description\r\nI run a besu node on Kubernetes cluster with persistent volume(pv). The data folder is stored in the pv. When the pod is deleted and created again besu gives following error.\r\n\r\n`org.rocksdb.RocksDBException: While lock file: /opt/besu/data/database/LOCK: No locks available`\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1.  start besu node in pod with pv\r\n2. delete pod \r\n3. start pod again.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\nThe besu should be able to reset db connection.\r\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happens]\r\nThe besu is not able to connect to db\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\neverytime.\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* docker image: hyperledger/besu:1.4.3\r\n\r\n### Additional info\r\nI thought it has to do with LOCK file. I delete the LOCK file before starting besu, still it doesn't solve the problem. \r\n",
